        "notes": "**AnchorForge Integrity Record (Inception Payload)**\n\nThis JSON object is a complete, self-contained SPV proof generated by AnchorForge. It includes:\n- The original anchored data (`original_audit_content` / `original_file_hash`)\n- The raw blockchain transaction (`raw_tx`)\n- The Transaction ID (`txid`)\n- The Merkle path (`merkle_proof`), acquired after block confirmation.\n\nTogether with a local block header, this structure allows cryptographically secure, off-chain verification of the data's integrity and timestamp. \nThis specific record serves as the payload for the AnchorForge Genesis 2 (Inception) transaction, demonstrating the protocol's ability to secure complex, nested audit trails.\n\n**AnchorForge v0.2: TLV Payload Decoder**\n\nThis Integrity Record contains a `raw_tx` hex string. To parse the AnchorForge OP_RETURN payload, look for `OP_FALSE OP_RETURN` followed by these Tag-Length-Value (TLV) blocks. \n\n**Tags (Hex / ASCII):**\n* `f0` (AppID): Identifies the AnchorForge protocol and version.\n* `48` ('H'): Hash of the anchored data (Prefix `00` = SHA256).\n* `50` ('P'): Public Key for ECDSA (Prefix `00` = Compressed).\n* `53` ('S'): ECDSA Signature (Prefix `01` = DER format).\n* `43` ('C'): X.509 Certificate (Prefix `01` = PEM format).\n* `44` ('D'): Embedded On-Chain Data (Prefix `00` = UTF-8, `01` = RAW).\n* `4e` ('N'): Transaction Note (Plain text).\n* `58` ('X'): External Reference / URI.\n\n**Parsing Rule:** [Push-Opcode] + [TAG] + [Length-Opcode] + [Prefix-Byte] + [Value]",
